The paper proposes a method for learning fine-grained image representations using a deep bilinear transformation block that can be stacked in convolutional neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed method is evaluated on several fine-grained image recognition benchmarks, which could suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of residual connections, which could also place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
